  <a href="#1" id="1">
   The Los Angeles Sports Council, in a bid to bring Super Bowl XXVII to the Rose Bowl in 1993,
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   will offer the stadium rent free to the National Football League along with all income from concessions and sales of novelty items.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   The Council selected the Rose Bowl because it has 103,083 seats.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   Under a joint agreement, Anaheim Stadium and the Coliseum did not submit bids
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   but they would share in the revenues if Pasadena gets the game.
  </a>
  <a href="#6" id="6">
   The share is still being negotiated.
  </a>
  <a href="#7" id="7">
   One plan calls for the Rose Bowl to receive 75% of the proceeds; the other two sharing 25%.
  </a>
